'''Sondre Klingen Langås''' (born 2 February 2001) is a Norwegian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for {{English football updater|DerbyCou}} club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

Langås made his debut in the Norwegian [[Eliteserien]] for [[Viking FK|Viking]]. He made his debut for [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in 2024.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Langås started his youth career in the rural club Spillum before moving on to [[Namsos IL|Namsos]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.t-a.no/5-divisjonsklubb-far-1-3-mill-etter-rekordovergang/s/5-116-2100197|title=5. divisjonsklubb får 1,3 mill. etter rekordovergang|date=3 February 2025|work=Trønder-Avisa|language=no|access-date=16 March 2025}}</ref> He then played in the [[Norwegian First Division]] for [[Ranheim Fotball|Ranheim]] and [[IL Stjørdals-Blink|Stjørdals-Blink]] (on loan from Ranheim).

===Viking===
In May 2023, Langås was wanted by [[Rosenborg BK]] and trained with the team, together with Ranheim teammate [[Ruben Alte]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.adressa.no/sport/fotball/i/jlbMxb/rbk-aapner-for-aa-hente-ranheim-duo-i-sommer|title=RBK åpner for å hente Ranheim-duo i sommer|date=11 May 2023|work=Adresseavisen|language=no|access-date=16 March 2025}}</ref> On 24 July 2023, he signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with [[Eliteserien]] club [[Viking FK|Viking]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vikingfotball.no/nyheter/sondre-langas-er-ny-viking-spiller|title=Sondre Langås er ny Viking-spiller|work=Viking FK|language=no|date=24 July 2023|access-date=18 August 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 13 August 2023 against [[Lillestrøm SK|Lillestrøm]].<ref name="nff"/> On 16 September 2023, he scored his first goal in a 2–0 away win over [[FK Haugesund|Haugesund]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dagsavisen.no/sport/fotball/2023/09/17/stoppervikar-langas-matchvinner-for-gulljagende-viking-ubeseiret-i-tolv-kamper/|title=Stoppervikar Langås matchvinner for gulljagende Viking – ubeseiret i tolv kamper|language=no|date=16 September 2023|access-date=17 September 2023}}</ref>

===Derby County===
On 1 February 2025, Langås joined [[EFL Championship|English Championship]] club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on a four-and-a-half-year contract<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-transfers-sondre-langas-9912290|title=Derby County complete third January transfer|language=en|date=1 February 2025|access-date=1 February 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dcfc.co.uk/news/2025/02/transfer-news-norwegian-international-defender-langas-signs-for-derby-county|title=TRANSFER NEWS: Norwegian international defender Langas signs for Derby County|website=www.dcfc.co.uk|date=1 February 2025|accessdate=1 February 2025}}</ref> for a fee reported to be in the region of {{NOK|60 million}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/den-norske-landslagsspilleren-sondre-langas-solgt-for-enorm-sum/s/5-95-2266535|title=Norsk landslagsspiller solgt for enorm sum|last=Tveito|first=Sjur|date=1 February 2025|work=Nettavisen|language=no|access-date=16 March 2025}}</ref> The move saw him reunite with former Viking teammate [[Lars-Jørgen Salvesen]] whom had joined the same club earlier in the transfer window. Langås made his Derby debut in a 1–1 draw at [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on 8 February 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cy4mw1nk3j8t |website=BBC Sport|title=Norwich City 1–1 Derby County| date=8 February 2025 |accessdate=15 May 2025}}</ref> In March 2025, Langås sustained a hamstring injury; however with the club in a relegation battle to stay in the Championship, he decided to delay surgery to the end the season with head coach [[John Eustace]] stating that Langås went through the "pain barrier" for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-hero-could-quite-10030857 |website=Derby Telegraph|title=Derby County hero could 'quite easily' have had surgery - but played injured vs Plymouth Argyle| date=17 March 2025 |accessdate=15 May 2025}}</ref> Langås became part of a back-three alongside [[Matthew Clarke (footballer, born 1996)|Matt Clarke]] and [[Nat Phillips]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/sondre-langas-delivers-perfect-response-10048673 |website=Derby Telegraph|title=Sondre Langas delivers perfect response after Derby County transfer was questioned| date=24 March 2025 |accessdate=15 May 2025}}</ref> which helped Derby finish 19th in the Championship and beat relegation by one point, with Langås making 14 appearances during his first season for Derby.<ref name="Soccerway">{{cite web|title=S. Langås|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/sondre-klingen-langas/659626/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 May 2025}}</ref> Langås said in July 2025 interview that he played through the pain barrier during the period, confirming what Eustace said in March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cnvmvj05yvro|website=BBC Sport|title='Hard to describe how painful injury was' - Langas| date=24 July 2025 |accessdate=27 January 2026}}</ref>

In June 2025, it was confirmed by Eustace that Langås would miss the start of the [[2025–26 Derby County F.C. season|2025–26 season]] due to rehabilitation from his knee surgery he had in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-injury-latest-news-10291944 |website=Derby Telegraph|title=Trio to miss start of Derby County season as fixtures release date looms| date=25 June 2025 |accessdate=26 June 2025}}</ref> Langås returned to first-team action on 21 October 2025 against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-norwich-talking-points-10589835|website=Derby Telegraph|title=What Sondre Langas did to £2m Norwich ace as John Eustace set for creative Derby County thinking| date=22 October 2025 |accessdate=27 January 2026}}</ref> On 22 November 2025, Langås scored his first goal for Derby in a 2–3 loss to [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c8x10j2j847t|website=BBC Sport|title=Derby County 2–2 Watford| date=22 November 2025 |accessdate=27 January 2026}}</ref> On 10 December 2025, Langås was named [[captain (association football)|captain]] for the first time in Derby's match against [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]], with club captain [[Lewis Travis]] being unavailable due to injury and vice-captain [[Ebou Adams]] being on the bench for the match, with Eustace stating his character being part of the decision to give him the armband.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-sondre-langas-captain-10702284
|website=Derby Telegraph|title=John Eustace explains Sondre Langas decision after being handed Derby County honour
| date=12 December 2025 |accessdate=27 January 2026}}</ref> In January 2026, Langås sustained a hamstring injury, which ruled him out for ten matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-langas-johnston-injuries-10900091|website=Derby Telegraph|title=Derby County duo ruled out of Easter double header against Coventry City and Stoke City
| date=2 April 2026 |accessdate=13 May 2026}}</ref> He made 25 apperances during his first full season in England, scoring three goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footballwebpages.co.uk/derby-county/appearances/2025-2026|title=Derby County – Appearances|publisher=Football Web Pages|date=13 May 2026|access-date=13 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Langås made his debut for the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] on 9 September 2024 in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]] game against Austria at [[Ullevaal Stadion]]. He substituted [[Alexander Sørloth]] in added time of Norway's 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698924/austria-norway|title=Norway v Austria game report|date=9 September 2024}}</ref>

Langås was named in Norway's [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-sondre-langas-norway-10979247|title=Derby County double confirmed after World Cup reveal as Sondre Langas says 'I didn't trust it'|publisher=Derby Telegraph|date=22 May 2026|access-date=25 May 2026}}</ref>

